entries.subTitle: Azienda Vitivinicola Il Colle, Prosecco Valdobbiadene DOC
entries.description:
• Grape variety: 90% Glera, 10% Chardonnay

  • Origin: Conegliano-Valdobbiadene DOC, Veneto, Italy

entries.name: Zuribieter
entries.subTitle: Weingut Landolt, Züribieter Cuvée Weiss 2023
entries.description:
• Grape variety: Blend Riesling-Silvaner (Müller-Thurgau), Pinot Gris, Sauvignon Blanc, Pinot Noir (Blanc de Noir)

  • Origin: Zurich, Switzerland

  • Profile: Fruit profile based on ripe yellow stone fruits like peaches and apricots,some tropical hints with just ripe pineapple and guava, Freshly squeezed lemon juice, Apple blossom and lemon balm

  • Style: Dry white, Fruit driven, delicate and tart to just ripe tropical aroma profile, Youthful and lightweighted

entries.name: Riesling Loersch
entries.subTitle: Weingut Alexander Loersch, Trittenheimer Altärchen 2023
entries.description:
• Grape variety: 100% Riesling

  • Origin: Mosel, Germany

  • Profile: Intense and ripe stone fruit flavors with lots of apricot, yellow peaches, Some tropica aromas with ripe lychee and kiwi, Ripe yellow apples, honeysuckle and lemon balm, Touch of pencil shavings, Saline texture

  • Style: Dry white with a hint of sweetness, Ripe fruit profile but well balanced by a sharp and juicy acidity, Fresh but with some depth and texture to it

entries.name: Zeter Chardonnay
entries.subTitle: Weingut Oliver Zeter, Haardt Chardonnay 2023

  • Style: Dry and mineral driven whiteChardonnay characteristic creamy texture with good acidity

entries.name: Anne Claire Schott, Pét-Nat Rosé 2021 - Bottle (7,5dl)
entries.subTitle: Anne Claire Schott, Pét-Nat - Bottle (0.75l)
entries.description:
• Grape variety: 85% Chasselas, 15% Muscat
  • Origin: Neuchâtel, Switzerland
  • Profile: Ripe citrus fruit, yellow apples, Honey & Beewax
  • Style: Natural - dry & fizzy


This creation of art, as Anne-Claire refers to her wines, was produced in Neuchâtel.


Given the heat and the cold winter in this area, the three lakes play an important role in moderating the climate.


All her vineyard work and winemaking techniques are based on biodynamic approaches, which is always resulting in very character driven wines.


This natural fizzy wine impresses with ripe citrus fruit accompanied by dried wildflowers and honey.


This creative craft - is always surprising!

entries.name: Still Water 1l
entries.subTitle: Water Still 1l
entries.description:
We serve still and sparkling water using a high-end BRITA system, designed for exceptional purity and taste.

Behind the scenes, it filters out microplastics, unwanted residues, and bacteria — the same hygiene standard used in healthcare. It's our way of offering clean, great-tasting water without single-use plastic.
